<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-65-1010 </DOCNO><TEXT>In this letter, the authors derive a formula of linewidth for a semi-conductor-opticalfiber ring laser by using coupled rate equations for the active and passivecavity. It shows that the linewidth is not only the function of the twocavity length ratio, time delay in fiber, but also the function of lightintensity ratio of the two cavities and the phase shift introduced byjunctions between the gain medium and the optical fiber.</TEXT></DOC>